-- Nasdaq extends losses on large-cap tech weakness
-- 
-- Tue Jan 20, 2009 1:57pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/20/us-markets-stocks-nasdaq4pct-idUSTRE50J6I320090120

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The Nasdaq composite extended losses and fell more than 4 percent on Tuesday, weighed down by a sell-off in large-cap technology companies, including Apple ( AAPL.O ), Microsoft ( MSFT.O ) and Google ( GOOG.O ). 

 Highlights: * Dow component IBM Corp ( IBM.N ) shares fell 1.2 percent to $83.88 ahead of its quarterly earnings due after the closing bell. * The Dow Jones industrial average  .DJI  was down 173.15 points, or 2.09 percent, at 8,108.07. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index  .SPX  was down 25.68 points, or 3.02 percent, at 824.44. The Nasdaq Composite Index  .IXIC  was down 57.20 points, or 3.74 percent, at 1,472.13. (Editing by  Chizu Nomiyama )